## Executive Summary

España con ACNUR is a prominent humanitarian donor with significant but
variable funding, contributing over \$100 million in 2025 across diverse
regions. Their funding is highly earmarked—about 39%—reflecting a
targeted approach concentrated in select strategic areas, notably East
Africa (Uganda, Chad, Rwanda, Ethiopia). While transaction volumes and
average amounts are lower and less frequent than peer donors, España con
ACNUR’s expanding geographic reach, growing from 8 to 23 countries
(2022–2025), signals increasing engagement. Fundraising strategies
should emphasize alignment with Spain’s earmarked priorities, address
funding concentration disparities, and explore opportunities to scale
transaction size and frequency to enhance program impact and resilience.

## Volatility

This visualization depicts the funding transactions for España con ACNUR
over time, comparing the average transaction value and frequency to a
benchmark group of the top 10 other donors. España con ACNUR conducts an
average of 181 transactions per year with an average transaction amount
of approximately 639,300 USD. In contrast, the benchmark group averages
370 transactions per year with an average transaction size of about 2.9
million USD, indicating that España con ACNUR provides smaller and less
frequent funding. The dataset consists of 543 transaction records
spanning from early 2023 through late 2025. Transaction values show
considerable volatility, with a wide range in amounts, as shown by the
plot points and smoothed trend lines. The lower transaction value and
frequency suggest limitations in financial flow consistency compared to

may impact program implementation speed and scale, warranting attention
in fundraising strategies. Increasing transaction size or frequency
could improve operational stability. Understanding these patterns is
